6 months ago, I opened LeetCode for the first time.
Stared at a "Easy" problem for 45 minutes.
Closed the tab.
That was my relationship with DSA for a long time.
Start. Get stuck. Quit. Repeat.
Not because I wasn't smart enough.
But because I was doing it alone.
No structure. No accountability. No one to say "bro, this is normal, keep going."
So I decided to build what I wished existed.
Today, I'm launching the DSA Partner Challenge — a free 60–70 day structured program for my community of 1700+ people where every single day I'll share:
→ The topic to cover
→ The best resource to learn it from
→ Practice questions to actually apply it
No paid course. No gatekeeping. Just consistency, structure, and people doing it together.
Week 1 starts with the basics — language revision (Java / Python / C++) and maths for DSA. Because most people don't fail DSA because it's hard. They fail because they never had a solid foundation.
If you've tried to learn DSA before and gave up — this is for you.
Everyday at 7 PM, I'm dropping the full 60–70 day plan.
Everything. Every topic. Every week. Laid out so you never have to wonder "what do I study next."
You don't have to figure it out alone anymore.
Drop a 🔥 if you want the plan — I'll make sure it reaches you.